'''''Folk Stories from Southern Nigeria''''' is a book published in 1910.

The book contains forty [[folklore|folk stories]] and [[fairy tales]] from [[Southern Nigeria Protectorate|Southern Nigeria]]. The stories were [[Folkloristics|collected]] by [[Elphinstone Dayrell]], then the [[Colonial_Service#Ranks|District Commissioner]] of the region. The book has an introduction by [[Andrew Lang]], famous for [[Andrew Lang's Fairy Books|his series of fairy books]].

