'''''The Serpent and the Rope''''' is a [[novel]] by [[Raja Rao]] first published in 1960 by [[John Murray (publisher)|John Murray]]. Written in an autobiographical style, the novel deals with the concepts of existence, reality, and fulfillment of one's capabilities.{{sfn|Gupta|2002|p=24–25}} The protagonist Ramaswamy's thought process in the novel is said to be influenced by [[Vedanta|vedantic]] philosophy and [[Adi Shankara]]'s non-dualism.{{sfn|Dayal|1986|p=21–28}}

The novel won the [[Sahitya Akademi Award]] in 1964.{{sfn|Powers|2003|p=212–213}}

